==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seductive
<hw>Se*duc"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to lead
astray; apt to mislead by flattering appearances; tempting; alluring;
<as>as, a <ex>seductive</ex> offer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This may enable us to understand how <qex>seductive</qex> is the
influence of example.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seductively</ent>⟦br⟧
